cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR

This paper deals with improving object localization in computer vision, which is a core topic in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of bounding box regression and clustering techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses evaluation rates and performance analysis, which are relevant to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of NMS (Non-Maximum Suppression) and bounding box techniques suggests a possible fit with the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category, which deals with techniques for secure and efficient computation.
